<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-01T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-01T19:00:00-05:00" n="774" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d774">
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_PWH1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Page</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-01T19:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">February 1, 1917, 7 p. m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>4377. See Consul London’s despatch 3474, January 17. Unofficially
                                inform Foreign Office that your representations based on <pb facs="0866" n="580" xml:id="pg_580"/> Department’s 4330, January
                                24, as to permits for needles of German origin to British houses is
                                confirmed by statement of Procurator General and that under
                                circumstances Department feels justified in expecting prompt
                                assurances of non-interference with needles covered by Department’s
                                instruction 4512,<note n="1" xml:id="d774fn1">
                                    <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_576">p.
                                    576</ref>.</note> November 25.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>